Question: Getting feedback from those around you is an effective way to develop your delegation technique.
Identify the examples of best practices for getting feedback on your delegation style.
Instruction: Choose all options that best answer the question. 

Assure your delegates that you value and respect what they have to say

Emphasize that you're genuine and serious about wanting to get better at delegation

Consider making it mandatory for team members to provide feedback

Ask each team member to comment on one other team member's feedback

Assure your team that you genuinely want to know what they think

Collect all of your delegates' responses and make an overall assessment
